<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbus=
iness.com/click/28884070.272571/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy90ZXR=
oZXItc2F5cy1hdWRpdC1pcy1zdGlsbC1tb250aHMtYXdheS1hcy1jcnlwdG8tbWFya2V0LWZhbH=
RlcnMtMTE2NjE1Njg5NzE_bW9kPWl0cF93c2omcnU9eWFob28/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB=
26ad4f2c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" =
style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wi=
dth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgro=
und-color: #ccc;"> article is from Saturday</a>, though it could be from an=
y time in the last five years:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Take Tether, the company behind the world=E2=
=80=99s largest stablecoin. In recent months, it launched a marketing blitz=
 of blogs and press releases, touting its transparency, after a series of c=
rypto firm failures rattled investor confidence in it. Tether is designed t=
o grease the rails of the roughly $1 trillion cryptocurrency market by prom=
ising each token can be redeemed for $1. Market observers have long questio=
ned whether the firm=E2=80=99s reserves are sufficient and have been demand=
ing audited information.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The company has been promising an audit since =
at least 2017. An audit is =E2=80=9Clikely months=E2=80=9D away, said Paolo=
 Ardoino, chief technology officer of Tether Holdings which issues the teth=
er coin that recently carried a market value of $68 billion.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThings are going slower than=E2=80=A6=
we would like,=E2=80=9D Mr. Ardoino said.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The basic situation with Tether is that it cla=
ims to be 100% backed by safe assets. Actually it claims to be about 100.3%=
 backed: For every $1 of Tether outstanding, there are about $1.003=C2=A0of=
 assets that Tether keeps in a box.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#foo=
tnote-2" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-=
bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none =
!important; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block=
;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a> But Tether is notoriously secretive about what it keeps in the box. Wh=
ereas a typical money-market fund will <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombe=
rgbusiness.com/click/28884070.272571/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcG=
luaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDctMjIvcHJpdmF0ZS1lcXVpdHktZmlybS1nb3QtcmljaC1tY=
WtpbmctcHJpdmF0ZS1lcXVpdHktZmlybXMtcmljaD9jbXBpZD1CQkQwODI5MjJfTU9ORVlTVFVG=
RiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMjA4Mjk=
mdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc58095fd" itempro=
p=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #=
000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-=
bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"=
>  list the exact dollar amount and CUSIP</a>=C2=A0of every instrument that=
 it owns, Tether discloses broad categories of securities; whereas banks an=
d money-market funds have audited accounts, Tether is perpetually months aw=
ay from the audit that will finally solve all of its problems.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And plainly Tether is=C2=A0<em>not </em>always=
=C2=A0100%, or 100.3%,=C2=A0backed by very safe assets. For one thing, even=
 its <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28884070.2725=
71/aHR0cHM6Ly90ZXRoZXIudG8vZW4vdHJhbnNwYXJlbmN5LyNyZXBvcnRz/607f07ceef4b852=
4a319a23cB5ca67136" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;"> current =E2=80=9Creserves breakdown,=E2=80=
=9D</a> as of June 30, 2022, says that 8.36% of its assets are in =E2=80=9C=
Other Investments (Including Digital Tokens),=E2=80=9D and digital tokens s=
ometimes lose value. If Tether=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9Cother investments=E2=80=
=9D lost 10% of their value, then Tether would no longer be fully backed: E=
ach Tether=C2=A0<em>was=C2=A0</em>backed by $1.003 of assets, but if 8% of =
its portfolio lost 10% of its value then it would=C2=A0be backed by only $0=
.995 of value. Cryptocurrencies lose 10% of their value all the time. Also =
there is some historical record of Tether counting risky loans =E2=80=94=C2=
=A0to <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28884070.272=
571/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTktMDQtMjY=
vdGhpbmdzLWdvdC13ZWlyZC1mb3Itc3RhYmxlY29pbi10ZXRoZXI_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDgyOTIyX0=
1PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlc=
m09MjIwODI5JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB479a16=
