<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The interesting question with Tether is: Let=
=E2=80=99s say that you=C2=A0<em>knew</em>, definitively, that Tether =E2=
=80=9Cbroke the buck.=E2=80=9D Some of its not-so-safe assets didn=E2=80=99=
t pan out, and each Tether turned out to only be backed by, say, 97 or 98 c=
ents of assets. In the world of <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/28884070.272571/aHR0cHM6Ly9lbi53aWtpcGVkaWEub3JnL3dpa2kvUmVzZ=
