or: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> money-ma=
rket funds</a> =E2=80=94=C2=A0or of regulated=C2=A0<em>banks=C2=A0</em>=E2=
=80=94=C2=A0that would be a disaster; that would be insolvency and a bank r=
un and the end of the fund and a possible systemic crisis. Investors put th=
eir dollar in expecting that they could always get exactly $1 back, and if =
they find out that they can=E2=80=99t then they=E2=80=99ll race to get thei=
r $1 while they still can, and the fund will be forced to liquidate its hol=
dings and further drive down their prices and leave investors with big loss=
es that they were not expecting.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In the world of stablecoins =E2=80=A6=C2=A0I d=
on=E2=80=99t know? It is not obvious that the same intuitions apply. The po=
int of a stablecoin is not=C2=A0<em>mainly=C2=A0</em>to be a secure claim o=
n $1 of assets in a bank account. The point of a stablecoin is mainly =E2=
=80=9Cto grease the rails of the roughly $1 trillion cryptocurrency market,=
=E2=80=9D by being the on-blockchain form of a dollar. We <a href=3D"https:=
//link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28884070.272571/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmx=
